<DOC><DOCNO> AP891230-0078 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-30-89 1345EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Uganda-Sudan     12-30 0194</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Uganda-Sudan,0200</SECOND><HEAD>Uganda Says Sudanese Attacked Border Town</HEAD><DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   State-controlled Radio Uganda claimedSaturday that Sudanese troops attacked a small Ugandan militarypost at the border town of Oraba, killing one soldier.   The broadcast quoted a Ministry of Defense statement as sayingthe Sudanese army troops struck the border post Friday morning andwere still in Ugandan territory at nightfall.   The report said the Sudanese troops were traveling in 16 trucksand supported by an armored personnel carrier and artillery. Itsaid the small border post detachment withdrew after one of itsmembers was killed in the attack. The Sudanese force then movedfarther into Ugandan territory, it added.   The report could not be independently verified.   Sudanese Embassy officials in Kampala refused to comment on thereport.   Sudan's army has been fighting an insurgency in the southernhalf of the country for nearly seven years, and the rebels oftencross into Uganda for sanctuary.   The Ugandan military high command has accused the Khartoumgovernment of ``aiding and abetting'' Ugandan guerrillas whooperate along the border.   In October, Uganda claimed several Sudanese warplanes bombedanother border town, Moyo, killing several civilians.</TEXT></DOC>